y the correlation between the MIR and\nX-ray continuum luminosities. The [SIV] emission line at 10.5 microns, which is\nbelieved to originate in the narrow line region, is detected in most AGN. We\nhave found an enhancement of the optical depth at 9.7 microns in the\nhigh-angular resolution data for higher values of NH. Clumpy torus models\nreproduce the observed values only if the host-galaxy properties are taken into\naccount.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Dec 2012 09:38:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
