 the\nlQCD calculations as well. Within the PHSD calculations, the strong maximum of\n\\zeta(T)/\\eta(T) close to T_c has to be attributed to mean-field (or potential)\neffects that in PHSD are encoded in the temperature dependence of the\nquasiparticle masses, which is related to the infrared enhancement of the\nresummed (effective) coupling g(T).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Dec 2012 10:55:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Jul 2013 09:01:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
